To install libsd2-dev on macOS, you can use MacPorts, a package manager for macOS. Here are the steps:

Install MacPorts by following the instructions on the MacPorts website

https://ports.macports.org/port/libsdl2/  

Open the Terminal application on your Mac. You can find it in the Utilities folder within the Applications folder.

Use MacPorts to install libsdl2 by running the following command in the terminal:

sudo port install libsdl2

After the installation is complete, you can verify that libsdl2 is installed by running the following command:

sdl2-config --version

This should display the version number of libsdl2 installed on your system

ANOTHER WAY TO INSTALL SDL2 ON MACOS

To install SDL2 on macOS using the terminal, you can follow these steps:

Open the Terminal application on your Mac. You can find it in the Utilities folder within the Applications folder.

Install Homebrew, a package manager for macOS, by running the following command in the terminal:

/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

Once Homebrew is installed, you can use it to install SDL2 by running the following command:

brew install sdl2

After the installation is complete, you can verify that SDL2 is installed by running the following command:

sdl2-config --version

This should display the version number of SDL2 installed on your system. Note that these steps assume you have a basic understanding of using the terminal on macOS. Homebrew simplifies the installation process by handling dependencies and ensuring the correct installation of SDL2.



